<p>Choosing the right words can feel daunting, but the intention behind the message holds more weight than perfect phrasing.  Simplicity, sincerity, and empathy are key. Whether delivered through a handwritten note, a card, an email, or a phone call, ensure your message conveys heartfelt sympathy and understanding.  Remembering to be mindful of the recipient's emotional state during this difficult time is vital.</p>
    

